def: A division of Hymenoptera including those which have anovipositor adapted for perforating plants. It includes the sawflies.
The act of depriving, as of furniture, apparatus, or agarrison. [R.]
To free from deafness; to cause to hear. [Obs.] Shak.
Either half of a square-rigged vessel's yard, from the centeror mast to the end.
A composition of passages detached from several differentcompositions; a potpourri.
A process of reasoning in which each conclusion applies to justsuch an object as each of the premises applies to. Jevons.

Making a beat without recoil; giving indications by a singlebeat or excursion; -- said of galvanometers and other instruments inwhich the needle or index moves to the extent of its deflection andstops with little or no further oscillation. Deadbeat escapement. Seeunder Escapement.
Of or pertaining to parricide; guilty of parricide.
